responses.content:
```yaml
leads:
  - headline: Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) via Image URL in jQuery Backstretch Plugin
    analysis: |
      The jQuery Backstretch plugin allows specifying image URLs dynamically. If user-supplied input is used to construct the image URL without proper sanitization, it could lead to a cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability. An attacker could craft a malicious URL containing JavaScript code, which would be executed in the context of the vulnerable web page when the image is loaded.
    cwe: CWE-79
    function_names:
      - show
    filenames:
      - scripts/jquery.backstretch.js
    classification: slightly promising
```
